{
  "document_id": "prov-13",
  "title": "Proverbs 13",
  "type": "study-bible",
  "translation": "Oxford",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-heading-14",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "14"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "From the fruit of their words good persons eat good things, but the desire of the treacherous is for wrongdoing."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-3",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "2 : See 12.14n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 2,
      "verse_end": 2
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "Those who guard their mouths preserve their lives; those who open wide their lips come to ruin."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "The appetite of the lazy craves, and gets nothing, while the appetite of the diligent is richly supplied."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-4",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "4 : , see 10.4n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 4,
      "verse_end": 4
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "The righteous hate falsehood, but the wicked act shamefully and disgracefully."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "Righteousness guards one whose way is upright, but sin overthrows the wicked."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "Some pretend to be rich, yet have nothing; others pretend to be poor, yet have great wealth."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "Wealth is a ransom for a person's life, but the poor get no threats."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-5",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "7–8 : Ironies about wealth and poverty, see 10.15n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 7,
      "verse_end": 8
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "The light of the righteous rejoices, but the lamp of the wicked goes out."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-6",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "9 : , a metaphor for life (e.g., 20.20; 24.20; Job 18.5–6).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 9,
      "verse_end": 9
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "By insolence the heedless make strife, but wisdom is with those who take advice."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "Wealth hastily gotten will dwindle, but those who gather little by little will increase it."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-7",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "11 : , see 1.18–19n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 11,
      "verse_end": 11
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "Hope deferred makes the heart sick, but a desire fulfilled is a tree of life."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-8",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "12 : , see 3.18n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 12,
      "verse_end": 12
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "Those who despise the word bring destruction on themselves, but those who respect the commandment will be rewarded."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-9",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "13 : See 10.2–3n.; cf. v. 18.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 13,
      "verse_end": 13
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "The teaching of the wise is a fountain of life, so that one may avoid the snares of death."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-10",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "14 : , see 10.11n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 14,
      "verse_end": 14
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "Good sense wins favor, but the way of the faithless is their ruin."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-11",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "15 : , see 2.22n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 15,
      "verse_end": 15
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "The clever do all things intelligently, but the fool displays folly."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "A bad messenger brings trouble, but a faithful envoy, healing."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-12",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "17 : were essential and highly valued in the ancient world. People relied on them to represent and communicate for them across vast distances, see 22.21; 25.13; 26.6.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 17,
      "verse_end": 17
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "Poverty and disgrace are for the one who ignores instruction, but one who heeds reproof is honored."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-13",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "18 : See v. 13.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 18,
      "verse_end": 18
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "A desire realized is sweet to the soul, but to turn away from evil is an abomination to fools."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-14",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "19 : See v. 12. , see 2.10n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 19,
      "verse_end": 19
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "Whoever walks with the wise becomes wise, but the companion of fools suffers harm."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "Misfortune pursues sinners, but prosperity rewards the righteous."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "The good leave an inheritance to their children's children, but the sinner's wealth is laid up for the righteous."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-15",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "21–22 : Punishment and reward extend to future generations; see Job 27.3–18.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 21,
      "verse_end": 22
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "The field of the poor may yield much food, but it is swept away through injustice."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-16",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "23 : , see 10.15n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 23,
      "verse_end": 23
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "Those who spare the rod hate their children, but those who love them are diligent to discipline them."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-17",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "24 : , see 10.13n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 24,
      "verse_end": 24
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "The righteous have enough to satisfy their appetite, but the belly of the wicked is empty."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-13-h1kj-1",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "10.1–22.16: The proverbs of Solomon. Comprised predominantly of two-line proverbs, the oldest section of Proverbs can be divided into 10.1–15.33, which features antithetical proverbs, and 16.1–22.16, which includes a mix of proverbial forms.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 13
      },
      "verse_start": 1,
      "verse_end": 25
    }
  ]
}